According to the documentation, when a user exceeds their query limit the API returns an error (HTTP 429 Too Many Requests) and includes rate-limit details. Example behaviors and data shown in the docs:

- HTTP status: 429 Too Many Requests.
- Response body example for monthly limit exceeded:
  {
    "success": false,
    "error": "Monthly query limit exceeded",
    "usage": {
      "current": 101,
      "max": 100,
      "exceeded": true,
      "reset_at": "2026-02-01T00:00:00Z"
    }
  }
  - usage fields: current (current count), max (allowed; -1 = unlimited), exceeded (boolean), reset_at (ISO 8601 monthly reset time).
- Rate-limit responses may also include an error object such as:
  {
    "error": {
      "code": "RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED",
      "message": "Rate limit exceeded. Try again in 60 seconds"
    }
  }
- Rate limit headers are included on responses (e.g. X-RateLimit-Limit, X-RateLimit-Remaining, X-RateLimit-Reset).

The docs also show other related error formats (e.g., an INSUFFICIENT_CREDITS error when query/credit limits are hit).

